caption: Puerto Rican from New York City. I think a Cuban sandwich is one of my favorite sandwiches.  This spot has a solid sandwich but needs help  Honest feedback - 1-change the ham or put less in the sandwich. Ham overpowered the taste 2-add a …

Such good food....incredibly kind owner and workers. I will remember this place! And they actually fill you up, unlike a thousand chains in LA that overcharge and underprovide. This place is fantastic.

All the food is great. I tried pretty much all of them. I love the Cuban Phillis sandwich, the mojo chicken bowl,  yuca frita, all the empanadas,  the potatoes fries, the brownies.  I love all of the sauces. My next gold is to try the mojo chicken sandwich and the Cuban sandwich  the service is really fast and professional

Wow this place is new and the food is amazing 😋 we ordered the Cuban sandwich, Philly sandwich, empanadas and yucca fries. It was mouthwatering and so yummy. The seasoning on the pork and the Ropa was on point. I crave for this food at least once a week. If you’re craving for some Cuban food, try this place!!!

Ordered here from Grubhub who messed up my order and cancelled it. Owner of restaurant reached out and sent the chef to my place to deliver my order even after I got a refund from Grubhub. So nice of them to go the extra mile. And the best …
Im Cuban (from sfl) and vegan and omg the vegan Cuban sandwich!! The bread is 👌 🇨🇺 🇨🇺 🇨🇺 So glad to have discovered this gem!!  I just wish they had mojo for the yuca that is the only thing!
